id: records/node
title: "records node"
kind: knowledge-node
status: v0-seed
updated: 2026-07-01

purpose: >
  Hold material time: access logs, LLM-used context, GitHub surfaces, backups,
  next-move ledgers, and proof-related records.

holds:
  - material time
  - access log
  - automation log
  - yawn.bot log
  - yawn.bot verification reports
  - llm access
  - github access
  - backup log
  - feedback log
  - next-move ledger

receives:
  - agent actions
  - automation runs
  - tool use
  - file access
  - external surfaces
  - proof and replay events
  - feedback emails

produces:
  - auditable memory
  - next-move rationale
  - recovery and provenance records
  - feedback records
  - automation records
  - bot service records
  - bot verification records

questions:
  - what happened materially
  - what did the agent use
  - what access shaped the next move
  - what backup or proof exists
  - what feedback has arrived
  - what automation was created or ran
  - what did yawn.bot observe or propose
  - what suggestion did a verification run produce

links:
  - records/material-time.yawn
  - records/access-log.yawn
  - records/automation-log.yawn
  - records/yawn.bot-log.yawn
  - records/yawn.bot-verification-2026-07-01.yawn
  - records/llm-access.yawn
  - records/github-access.yawn
  - records/backup-log.yawn
  - records/feedback-log.yawn
  - records/next-move-ledger.yawn

proof:
  source:
    - records/material-time.yawn
    - records/automation-log.yawn
    - records/yawn.bot-log.yawn
    - records/yawn.bot-verification-2026-07-01.yawn
    - records/feedback-log.yawn
